cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for pedestrian detection in autonomous driving. It also involves robotics (RO) and artificial intelligence (AI) in the context of autonomous driving. Additionally, the use of multispectral images involves multimedia (MM) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.RO, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
